tars are\ncommon, but predictions of the merger fraction are highly sensitive to the\ncriterion used to decide whether two protostars should merge. Previous studies\nof Population III star formation have often considered only one realization per\nset of initial conditions. However, our results demonstrate that robust trends\ncan only be reliably identified by considering averages over a larger sample of\nruns.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Dec 2019 09:54:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Jan 2020 10:46:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-12"}
